    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_3816f0a8",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/be/impl/ActivitySpecManagerImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 191,
      "message": "Won't it be simpler to use something along the following lines?\n\nprivate static final Map<VersionStatus, TransitionData> VALIDATE_STATUSES = \nnew EnumMap<>(); // then put Certified, Deprecated, Deleted along with corresponding TransitionData, which is an inner class\n\nVersionStatus status = version.getStatus();\nTransitionData transition = VALIDATE_STATUSES.get(status);\nif (prevStatus != null) {\n        String errMsg = String.format(\"%s ActivitySpec With Id %s failed since it is not in %s status\", transition.getAction(), activitySpecId, status);\n        validateStatus(Objects.nonNull(retrievedVersion) ? retrievedVersion.getStatus() : null, status, errMsg);\n        prevVersionStatus = transition.getPrevStatus();\n}",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-06 16:49:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_180f7489",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/be/impl/ActivitySpecManagerImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 228,
      "message": "Again, don't remove such a useful piece information as stack the exception's trace. And provide some message to understand the context the error happened in.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-06 16:49:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_d824ac0e",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/be/impl/ActivitySpecManagerImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 253,
      "message": "Seems like the pattern \"itemPredicate = item -> ItemType.activityspec.name().equals(item.getType())\n            && item.getVersionStatusCounters().containsKey(status)\" repeats. So why not just to pass the status? And if you need to do it only for particular statuses, just create a constant that lists them. It has at least two advantages: 1) you don't have to repeat the same code; 2) it's easy to add/remove statuses if needed.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-06 16:49:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_387d90e8",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/main/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/utils/ActivitySpecConstant.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 28,
      "message": "It's about instantiation. The private constructor makes it impossible to call new ActivitySpecConstant(), which make the class explicitly a collection of constants and static methods.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-06 16:49:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_b870c00b",
      "file_path": "services/activity-spec/activity-spec-web/activity-spec-service/src/test/java/org/openecomp/activityspec/be/dao/impl/ActivitySpecZusammenDaoImplTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 10,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "Don't use members in tests.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
      },
      "updated": "2018-03-06 16:49:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
